  "It changes every month": "",
  "The Moon rotates so all sides face Earth equally": "",
  "The far side": "",
  "The near side, due to tidal locking": "",
  "The Moon is tidally locked to Earth, meaning its rotational period equals its orbital period. As a result, the same side (the near side) always faces Earth, and the far side is never visible from Earth's surface.": "",
