  "An eclipse visible only from the Southern Hemisphere": "",
  "A solar eclipse where the Moon is too far from Earth to completely cover the Sun, leaving a bright ring visible": "",
  "A lunar eclipse that lasts for several hours": "",
  "An eclipse that occurs annually on the same date": "",
  "An annular solar eclipse occurs when the Moon is near apogee (its farthest point from Earth), making it appear slightly smaller than the Sun. The Moon cannot fully cover the solar disk, leaving a bright ring (annulus) of sunlight visible around the Moon.": "",
