  "A supermoon; the Moon appears red when it is closest to Earth": "",
  "A new moon; reflected light from Mars turns the Moon red": "",
  "A solar eclipse; the Sun turns the Moon red": "",
  "A 'blood moon' occurs during a total lunar eclipse when Earth's shadow completely covers the Moon. Earth's atmosphere bends (refracts) sunlight around the planet, filtering out blue wavelengths and allowing red wavelengths to reach and illuminate the Moon.": "",
  "Ancient civilizations used lunar calendars based on the Moon's cycle of phases. If a culture defines a month as one complete lunar cycle, approximately how many days would each month contain?": "",
  "Approximately 35 days": "",
  "Approximately 25 days": "",
  "Approximately 29.5 days": "",
  "Approximately 31 days": "",
  "A lunar month based on the Moon's synodic period lasts approximately 29.5 days. Many ancient calendars, including Islamic and Hebrew calendars, use months that alternate between 29 and 30 days to approximate this cycle.": "",
