  "The Sun's diameter is roughly 400 times larger than the Moon's, but it is also approximately 400 times farther from Earth. This remarkable coincidence means both objects appear nearly the same angular size (about 0.5 degrees) in our sky, enabling total solar eclipses.": "",
  "A science teacher asks students to explain why we never see the far side of the Moon from Earth. One student says the Moon does not rotate. Is this explanation correct?": "",
